com.wm.app.tn.doc
Class BizDocContentPart

java.lang.Object
  com.wm.app.tn.util.TNFixedData
      com.wm.app.tn.doc.BizDocContentPart
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.wm.data.IData, java.lang.Cloneable
public class BizDocContentPart
extends TNFixedData

Represents the content part that is associated with a BizDocEnvelope. Each BizDocEnvelope can have 0 or more content parts. BizDocContentPart can be used to represent small or large document parts. Some notes about small and large document parts:

  • If this represents a small content part then the "Bytes" field contains the content of the content part.
  • If this represents a large document part then the "Bytes" field is left empty (i.e. null) and the StorageType and StorageRef feilds carry more information about the actual content of the part. When the content of the part is temporarily stored in the TSpace system, the StorageType field contains the value of the constant, STORAGE_TYPE_TSPACE and the StorageRef field contains an object of com.wm.util.tspace.Reservation
In general, there are setters and getters for all the fields. None of the setters will modify the contents of the database unless explicitly stated otherwise: this means it's a bad idea to update documents after they've been saved.

See Also:
BizDocEnvelope
